The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, December 31, 2003 				 Pak love story unveiled in Indian school 
 Dubai, Dec. 30 (PTI): A  Pakistani boy was held in Riyadh for masquerading as a woman  to meet a girl studying in International Indian School in  the Saudi capital.																								In a bid to beat the kingdoms strict gender segregation rules, the boy in a veil along with his purported husband visited the school and asked to see a girl studying in the 11th grade. 																								However, the security guards became suspicious as the husband seemed very young and the veiled wife appeared too masculine.																								When challenged, the husband ran away, leaving the wife to be unmasked as the Pakistani boy, media reports said.																								The boy told the police that it was all a joke.
